c: 35
v: 18
t: "No burdened [soul] may bear anotherÂṀs burden: if some overladen soul should call out for someone else to carry his load, no one would bear any part of it even though he were a near relative. You can only warn those who dread their Lord although [He is] Unseen, and keep up prayer. Anyone who purifies himself, only purifies his own soul. Towards God should lie oneÂṀs goal"